Former president Jacob Zuma’s son, Duduzane is expected to shed light on his relationship with the Gupta family at the State Capture Inquiry on Monday.    Several witnesses have implicated Zuma junior of being present or arranging meetings at the Gupta family residence in Saxonwold in Johannesburg. Former Deputy Finance Minister Mcebisi Jonas testified before the commission that Duduzane – introduced him to the controversial family – at their Saxonworld home in 2015. He told the commission that one of the Gupta brothers offered him the position of Finance minister for R600-million… “He also said that if I worked with them I would become very rich and that he could immediately offer me R600-million. He pointed at Mr. Duduzane and said that they had made him a billionaire and that he had bought a house in Dubai.” Click on the video below: 